# Cortex agent — in-container job scheduler (supercronic crontab).
#
# WHERE THIS LIVES
#   This file is seeded on first start to:
#       /app/data/cron/crontab
#   /app/data is a persistent Docker volume (cortex-data), so any entries you
#   add here survive container restarts AND image upgrades. This baked copy
#   (/usr/local/share/cortex/crontab.default) is only used to seed the volume
#   the first time; after that the volume copy is authoritative.
#
# HOW IT RUNS
#   Loaded automatically at container startup by docker-entrypoint.sh and run
#   by supercronic as the non-root 'app' user (uid 1654) with the container's
#   environment. supercronic watches this file (-inotify) and hot-reloads it
#   whenever you edit it — no container restart needed.
#
# FORMAT (standard cron, 5 fields; supercronic also accepts an optional 6th
# "year" field and a leading "seconds" field for finer schedules):
#
#   ┌── minute (0-59)
#   │ ┌── hour (0-23)
#   │ │ ┌── day of month (1-31)
#   │ │ │ ┌── month (1-12)
#   │ │ │ │ ┌── day of week (0-6, Sunday=0)
#   │ │ │ │ │
#   * * * * * command-to-run
#
# EXAMPLES (uncomment / add your own below):
#   # Prune agent logs older than 14 days, every day at 03:00
#   0 3 * * * find /app/data/logs -type f -mtime +14 -delete
#
#   # Heartbeat every 5 minutes (shows up in `docker logs cortex-agent`)
#   */5 * * * * echo "cortex scheduler heartbeat"
#
# No schedules are defined by default — the scheduler starts and idles until
# you add entries here.
